from adjustText import adjust_text

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 8))
for team_name, team_df in df.groupby('team_name'):
    for i, player in team_df.iterrows():
        ax.scatter(player['ratings'], player['goals'], s=player['goals']*20, alpha=0.5, label=team_name)

# Add labels and legend
ax.set_xlabel('Player Ratings')
ax.set_ylabel('Goals Scored')
ax.set_title('Player Ratings vs. Goals Scored')

# add player name labels with adjust_text
texts = []
for i, player in df.iterrows():
    texts.append(ax.text(player['ratings'], player['goals'], player['name'], ha='center', va='center'))
adjust_text(texts, arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='-', color='gray'), expand_points=(1.2, 1.2), expand_text=(1.2, 1.2), force_points=0.1)

# move the legend outside the plot bbox
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')

# Display the plot
plt.show()

query="""
SELECT t.team_name, p.name, ps.goals
FROM team t
JOIN plays_for pf ON pf.team_id = t.team_id
JOIN player p ON p.player_id = pf.player_id
JOIN player_stats ps ON ps.player_id = p.player_id
JOIN (
  SELECT pf.team_id, MAX(ps.goals) AS max_goals
  FROM player_stats ps
  JOIN plays_for pf ON pf.player_id = ps.player_id
  GROUP BY pf.team_id
) AS max_stats ON max_stats.team_id = t.team_id AND max_stats.max_goals = ps.goals;
"""
cursor.execute(query)
results = cursor.fetchall()
df_mvp = pd.DataFrame(results, columns=cursor.column_names)

staff_collection = db["staff"]

# Define the pipeline stages for the aggregation query
pipeline = [
  # Lookup the team information for each staff member
  {
    "$lookup": {
      "from": "team",
      "localField": "team_id",
      "foreignField": "team_id",
      "as": "team"
    }
  },
  # Unwind the team array to flatten the documents
  { "$unwind": "$team" },
  # Group by team and compute average and total staff salary
  {
    "$group": {
      "_id": "$team.team_id",
      "team_name": { "$first": "$team.team_name" },
      "avg_salary": { "$avg": "$staff_salary" },
      "total_salary": { "$sum": "$staff_salary" }
    }
  }
]

# Execute the aggregation query and print the results
result = list(staff_collection.aggregate(pipeline))
for doc in result:
    print(doc)
df = pd.DataFrame(result)

player_collection = db["player"]

# Define the pipeline stages for the aggregation query
pipeline = [
  # Lookup the position information for each player
  {
    "$lookup": {
      "from": "player_position",
      "localField": "position_id",
      "foreignField": "position_id",
      "as": "position"
    }
  },
  # Unwind the position array to flatten the documents
  { "$unwind": "$position" },
  # Group by position and count the number of players
  {
    "$group": {
      "_id": "$position.position_id",
      "position_name": { "$first": "$position.type" },
      "count": { "$sum": 1 }
    }
  }
]

# Execute the aggregation query and print the results
result = list(player_collection.aggregate(pipeline))
for doc in result:
    print(doc)
df = pd.DataFrame(result)

# select database and collections
db = client["FootballManagement"]
player = db["player"]
team = db["team"]
plays_for = db["plays_for"]

# define the aggregation pipeline
pipeline = [
    {
        "$lookup": {
            "from": "player",
            "localField": "player_id",
            "foreignField": "player_id",
            "as": "player"
        }
    },
    {
        "$lookup": {
            "from": "team",
            "localField": "team_id",
            "foreignField": "team_id",
            "as": "team"
        }
    },
    
    {
        "$sort": {
            "contract_value": -1
        }
    },
    {
        "$project": {
            "player.name": 1,
            "team.team_name": 1,
            "contract_value": 1,
            "_id": 0
        }
    }
]

# execute the aggregation pipeline and save the result to a DataFrame
result = list(plays_for.aggregate(pipeline))
for doc in result:
    print(doc)

df = pd.DataFrame(result)

In [108]:
db = client["FootballManagement"]
player = db["player"]
player_stats = db["player_stats"]
pipeline = [
    {
        "$lookup": {
            "from": "player",
            "localField": "player_id",
            "foreignField": "player_id",
            "as": "player"
        }
    },
    {
        "$group": {
            "_id": "$player.name",
            "total_assists": {"$sum": "$assists"}
        }
    },
    
    {
        "$sort": {
            "total_assists": -1
        }
    }
]

result = list(player_stats.aggregate(pipeline))
for doc in result:
    print(doc)
df = pd.DataFrame(result)
